data.description: Looking for a vibrant neighborhood with access to outdoor activities and city life?  2639 Eastern Ave is the perfect  home located in a prime location across from Patterson Park.   Here are Features and Amenities: LOCATION: The home is situated on Eastern Avenue, right across from the Park, offering beautiful park views and access to open park space, dog park, athletic fields, community events, music in the park, community pool and ice rink, and so much more.  LAYOUT:  2639  is a wonderfully spacious home featuring 3 bedrooms and 1.5 baths. It's a middle-of-group row home  which retains some of its historical charm with original wood floors in stunning condition and  architectural details throughout; while also offering all modern amenities.  KITCHEN: The kitchen is huge and well-equipped with floor-to-ceiling pantry cabinets, black leathered granite countertops, a white subway tile backsplash, and 2 years young stainless steel appliances, including a 5-burner gas range, a new fridge, dishwasher, and built-in microwave. The kitchen also has a butcher block island (which conveys) for additional workspace.  The main level half bath is just off the kitchen.  UPPER LEVELl: Upstairs, there are three bedrooms, all featuring original wood floors. The primary bedroom includes a bay window that overlooks Patterson Park, providing a scenic view.  Bedroom #2 is perfect for an office or den while Bedroom #3 is adjacent to the light filled and spacious full bath.  BASEMENT: The finished basement has a front section perfect for an additional bedroom or a recreation room. The rear portion of the basement contains a laundry area with cabinets and counter space, as well as an open space suitable for a workshop or storage.  BACKYARD: The backyard is privately fenced and hardscaped with pavers. It features a raised bed for gardening and offers a great space for outdoor dining and entertainment.  PARKING: Parking is convenient on Eastern Avenue, with the Park across the street, plenty of spaces available.    WHAT A GREAT PLACE TO LIVE:  Canton eateries and nightspots throughout the neighborhood,  convenient shopping,  Patterson Park right across the street, convenient to downtown, shuttle to Hopkins, and minutes to 95.  Come make 2639 Eastern Ave, Your Home.
